data.enText: the quality of being exact, accurate and careful

data.chText: 以数学般的精确完成的

data.enText: Historians can't estimate the date with any (degree of) precision .
data.chText: 历史学家无法准确估算这个日期。

data.enText: He chose his words with precision .

simple_means.memory_skill: precise 精确的 + -ion 行为,状态

tr: the quality of being reproducible in amount or performance
example: he handled it with the preciseness of an automaton
note the meticulous precision of his measurements

example.tran: 唱诗班的演唱准确无误。

example.ex: The interior is planned with a precision the military would be proud of.
example.tran: 内部设计一丝不苟，足以让军方引以为豪。

value.def: If you do something with precision, you do it exactly as it should be done.
